{"id":42910,"date":"2025-03-09T13:44:55","date_gmt":"2025-03-09T09:44:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=42910"},"modified":"2025-03-09T13:44:55","modified_gmt":"2025-03-09T09:44:55","slug":"best-salat-al-duha","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/09\/best-salat-al-duha\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Duha: Best time for forenoon prayer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Zayd ibn Arqam reported: He saw some people performing the forenoon prayer, and he said, \u201cThey already know that prayer at a different time is better.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>The forenoon prayer of the penitent is when young camels can feel the heat of the sun.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 784<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Nawawi commented, \u201cOur scholars said this is the best time to perform the forenoon prayer, although it is permissible to do so after the sun rises until it reaches its zenith.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sharh\u0323 al-Nawawi\u0304 \u2018ala\u0301 S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 6\/30<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0642\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0649 \u0642\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064b\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0636\u0651\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0649 \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0642\u064e\u062f\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0651\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0629\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a \u063a\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0647\u064e\u0630\u0650\u06